  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9c\u0dda \u0db4\u0dde\u0daf\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0d9a \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dc3\u0da7 \u0d9c\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dd2 \u0dad\u0dd0\u0db6\u0dd6 \u0dad\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dd9\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d85\u0dad\u0dca\u0d85\u0da9\u0d82\u0d9c\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Three arrested for setting fire to Prime Minister's private house",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Police Media Spokesman Senior Superintendent of Police Advocate Nihal Talduwa said that three persons have been arrested by the Kollupitiya Police in connection with the incident of setting fire to the private house of Prime Minister Ranil Wickramasinghe.",
        "Among those arrested are a 19-year-old Galkissa resident and two Galle residents aged 24 and 28, the media spokesman said.",
        "The media spokesperson added that Kollupitiya police will conduct further investigations to arrest the other suspects."
      ],
